{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501203","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501203"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:25:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:25:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1733"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1733","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1733"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.1,0.34,0.16,0.39]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1733"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43552"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1733","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1733"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1733"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28565"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"385"},{"type":"tags","id":"904"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"1110"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"3813"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9097"},{"type":"tags","id":"9118"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"278"},{"type":"contributions","id":"635"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13665"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43552","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43552"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a two-day history of absolute constipation preceded by a one-month history of increasing constipation. On examination, his abdomen is distended and soft, apart from some localised tenderness in the right iliac fossa. Nothing abnormal can be felt on rectal examination and no faecal material can be felt. A plain abdominal X-ray shows gas in distended large bowel as far as the sigmoid colon where there is a sharp cut-off and no gas in the rectum.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Proctoscopy","Rigid sigmoidoscopy","Flexible sigmoidscopy","Gastrograffin enema","CT abdomen"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient almost certainly has a stenosing carcinoma of the distal colon and the localised tenderness in the right iliac fossa is a worrying sign of critical distension of the caecum. This patient will almost certainly require earlier surgical intervention - not just to overcome the obstruction, but to minimise the risk of rupture of the caecum.The initial investigation should be a \u003Cstrong\u003ECT scan.\u003C/strong\u003E This will rapidly identify both the site and the nature of the obstruction. Ideally, the scan should even precede the plain abdominal X-ray.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe obstructing lesion is certainly beyond the reach of a \u003Cstrong\u003Eproctoscope\u003C/strong\u003E and may be beyond the reach of the \u003Cstrong\u003Erigid sigmoidoscope.\u003C/strong\u003E The insufflation associated with \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexible sigmoidoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E might lead to frank caecal perforation. A \u003Cstrong\u003Egastrograffin\u003C/strong\u003E enema may help define the site of the lesion, but more information will be obtained from the CT scan.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["CT imaging plays a key role in identifying the site and underlying nature of cases of intestinal obstruction."],"references":["Catena F, De Simone B, Coccolini F, Di Saverio S, Sartelli M, Ansaloni L. Bowel obstruction: a narrative review for all physicians. World J Emerg Surg. 2019;14:20.  Available at: https://wjes.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13017-019-0240-7","Jackson PG, Raiji M. Evaluation and Management of Intestinal Obstruction. Am Fam Physician 2011; 83:159-65. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30215917/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28565"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1733"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28565","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28565"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-03-22T15:39:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-03-22T15:39:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1733"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43552"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-15T15:37:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","i